 Software Requirements
 Operating System:
o Windows 10 or later (64-bit preferred)
o Popular Linux distributions (e.g., Ubuntu, Fedora) with kernel versions
compatible with low-level drivers
 Programming Languages and Frameworks:
o C/C++ for low-level system hooks and kernel driver development
o Python or JavaScript (for the user interface and remote management
components)
 Database:
o Lightweight encrypted database (e.g., SQLite with encryption extensions) for
secure local log storage
 Encryption Libraries:
o OpenSSL or similar for encrypting logs and securing remote transmissions
 Network Protocols:
o Secure communication protocols such as TLS/SSL for remote log retrieval and
command & control channels
 User Interface:
o Cross-platform UI frameworks (e.g., Electron, Qt) for the control panel
 Security Software Compatibility:
o Must be tested for compatibility and stealth against common antivirus and
endpoint protection solutions
 Development Tools:
o Integrated Development Environments (IDEs) like Visual Studio, GCC
toolchain, and debugging tools for kernel-mode and user-mode development
 Logging and Monitoring Tools:
o Tools for real-time monitoring, anomaly detection, and alert generation
integrated within the software or accessible via API
